============================================================================
SANCTUM Information Retrieval Module for Indexing and Searching Twitter Data
============================================================================

There are 2 ways to run the module:
    - Using native Java (does not require Hadoop or the HDFS)
	- Using the Hadoop Job Scheduler and HDFS (requires that the HDFS has been installed)

=============
Configuration
=============

Check a file named 'config.cfg' for changing flags
for indexing the Twitter data.

========================================
Setup (if automatic setup does not work)
========================================

Hadoop:
	- Create a new folder in the root directory of the HDFS called 'sanctum'
	- Create a new folder inside /sanctum called 'data'
	- Put your data files into the /sanctum/data directory.
	- Run these commands in order:
		- hadoop jar SANCTUM-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar com.sanctum.drivers.HadoopDocSplit
		- hadoop jar SANCTUM-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar com.sanctum.drivers.HadoopIndex